snippet.textDisplay:
When you switch to using a password manager, you have to login to all your accounts and change your password to a new password generated by the manager. I defaulted to a length of 32 characters for whatever reason.

When you do that, you find out which websites have character limits, and it's always financial sites which should be the most secure. Random internet forum? 100 character password. Bank? 15-25 char password.

This is bad as there are only two possible reasons for it:
1. Passwords are stored in plain text so size in DB is a factor (hashed passwords are the same size regardless of length)
2. Some legacy system somewhere in the pipeline has the character limit.

Both are security problems.
